---
title: Balsamic-Glazed Meatloaves with Thyme-Roasted Brussels Sprouts & Sweet Potato Jumble
description: We adore the comfort of meatloaf, which can easily be dressed up with whatever flavors we’re craving. In this fun riff on the classic, individual pork meatloaves are coated with a sweet-tangy-savory balsamic-plum glaze, and served with a pile of crisp, roasted sweet potatoes, red onion, and Brussels sprouts—indulgent and satisfying. It’s all about live, laugh, loaf!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/balsamic-glazed-pork-meatloaves-aabef78e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64aecfd550e72558afc4f9ee.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/balsamic-glazed-meatloaves-64aecfd550e72558afc4f9ee
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 770 kcal
  fat: 43 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 68 g
  sugar: 33 g
  protein: 31 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 1000 mg
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: North America
---

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}. Halve and peel @Red Onion{1}; slice into ½-inch-thick wedges. Finely chop a few wedges until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Dice @Sweet Potatoes{1} into ½-inch pieces.

Toss Brussels sprouts on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, half the @Dried Thyme{1%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings), @salt{}, and pepper. Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

In a large #bowl{}, combine @Ground Beef{10%ounce}, garlic, @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon}, half the chopped onion, and 1 TBSP water (2 TBSP for 4 servings); season generously with @salt{}(generous) (we used ½ tsp; 1 tsp for 4) and @pepper{}.

Form pork mixture into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4); flatten tops.

> Swap in beef for pork.

Once Brussels sprouts have roasted ~{5%minutes}, remove sheet from oven. Carefully place meatloaves on opposite side of baking sheet.

On a second baking sheet, toss sweet potato and onion wedges with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast Brussels sprouts and meatloaves on top rack and sweet potatoes and onion wedges on middle rack until meatloaves are cooked through and veggies are lightly browned, ~{18-20%minutes}.

While everything roasts, heat a drizzle of oil in a medium pan over medium-high heat. Add remaining chopped onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @Balsamic Vinegar{5%teaspoon}; cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid has absorbed, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in ½ cup water (1 cup for 4 servings), @Plum Jam{2%unit}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, ¼ tsp salt (½ tsp for 4), and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until glaze begins to thicken, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted.

Transfer meatloaves to a #cutting board{} and let cool for ~{1%minute}; slice crosswise.

Divide meatloaves and veggies between plates. Spoon balsamic glaze over meatloaves and serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.